svg.title: Clouds of the genera Altocumulus, Altostratus and Nimbostratus: Altocumulus translucidus in bands, or one or more layers of altocumulus translucidus or opacus, progressively invading the sky; these altocumulus clouds generally thicken as a whole
svg.desc: WMO international weather symbol: Clouds of the genera Altocumulus, Altostratus and Nimbostratus: Semi-transparent altocumulus in bands, or altocumulus, in one or more fairly continuous layer (semi-transparent or opaque), progressively invading the sky; these altocumulus clouds generally thicken as a whole
